TestAuditAccumulatesHandledAndUnhandledErrors
/ Three handled errors plus one unhandled in a single foreach iteration produces %!callStack.Audit.Count% == 4. Each ThrowItem invocation throws a different error; the test goal's outer handler catches the unhandled one.
- set %items% = ["a", "b", "c", "d"]
- foreach %items%, call ThrowItem item=%item%, on error set %finalCaught% = true
- assert %finalCaught% is true
- set %auditCount% = %!callStack.Audit.Count%
- assert %auditCount% equals 4
